values:
Soooo I made a new livejournal cause I felt like having a different name. 

So if some random person humanxtsunami adds you as their friend, it's me.

I'm going to go do college stuff now.

<3

Sooo I'm posting again. See? Aren't you proud of me?

Just kidding.

Anyway, I'm sick. Yesterday I felt awful- I was on advil every 4 hours on the dot, I felt like a train ran over me, my throat and head hurt, I was dizzy and felt disconnected, I had a fever, bad chills, and I was just exhausted. I managed to drive myself to the doctors who's first guess was strep (it was mine too). But the test came back negative for strep. So the next most likely thing was mono, and they subjected me to the torture of a blood test (I hate needles) to check for that, and also took another throat culture to check for strep, tonsilitis, etc.

All I could think was, 'Just great. Epstein-Barr. I make out with one guy- one single, solitary guy, and I get mono. I must have gotten it some other way, but everyone is going to hammer me for this'. Which of course they did.

But none of that matters because my lab work came back today and my lymphocytes weren't elevated, hence no viral infection, just a bacterial one. I've never been so excited to hear that I had strep. I still sound horrible and my throat hurts and right now I'm exhausted but I still feel a lot better. And the antibiotics will have me better in at most 4 days (that's how long it took last time I had strep) and that's so much better than the 3-4 weeks it would have taken me to just get over this bout of mono, not to mention the months it would have taken me to reclaim my former hyper self, during soccer season and senior year which would have really sucked.

So the fact that I have an infection and can't see anyone for a few days and am under house arrest until then really doesn't bother me. 

But it does kinda suck that when we go to Florida I can't have a 'mono attack' and 'need' a wheelchair, then conviniently able to skip lines. Oh well.  Ankle injury it is.

I haven't posted in forever. I'm so lazy. But it's the summer and I have a ridiculous amount of summer work to do so I cant' be that lazy. I have to read 7 books, do 3 tests (or is it 4?) for Calculus and then do 2 history tests. And my moronic cleaners threw out my history stuff so I'm basically screwed. 

Still, this summer has been worth waiting for. It's been a very eventful one. The days drag on and though sometimes I'm bored it's never mind numbing horrible boring. The worst part of the summer was when I had to go to Massachusetts for a week, because it was soooo long. I wanted to be home, hanging out with my friends and a certain boy and instead I was stuck with little phone service, next to no internet access, and I was constantly woken up at pre-dawn hours like 8 and 9 o'clock.

I did see Tufts though. I really like Tufts. I also really like UPenn. Amherst and Williams didn't do much for me. I still need to see Cornell, Colgate, Bucknell, Gettysburg...maybe Northwestern, Notre Dame...I don't know. I still haven't found THE college, and I now suddenly I'm rethinking the one criteria I had for college- out of New Jersey. I want to get away from my home. I'll miss my friends, but they're all going away too, so that doesn't matter. But now as it gets closer, as it gets realer, I wonder if I shouldn't stay close to home just in case. I'll feel so guilty leaving my mom and brothers in the clutches of my father. So now I'm stuck with a dilemma- do I do what I think is best personally for me, or do I sacrifice what I want for my family? I know I should sacrifice for my family, but I wonder if in the long run it would be worse.

So chances are...I'll apply to all those schools, and go to the closest one that I get into. Hopefully UPenn. 2 hours isn't far. And I really like it.

Oh well we shall see what happens.

At least this post wasn't obsessing over guys. I'm serious. Girls may be confusing to guys, but guys are so confusing as well. My feelings are pretty confusing too. Arrgh.

-Katie

The most important thing of the last forensics competition was not my placement, nor the attentions of Presner, nor the hotness of Bennett, nor Liz trying to hunt down Travis.

No.

It was that the Mount got SECOND overall, which is our best placement since Gods-know-when.  SECOND only to Ridge.

WE TOTALLY CASTRATED SETON HALL!

So today was the monthly torture known as forensics.  I woke up at 7 to get dressed (I got a new shirt, and it totally rocked), put my hair up in braids (wanted something different), ate, and then rushed out to go to Montville.  I got stuck behind some fucker who was driving like TWENTY FIVE in a 30 or 35 and I was most displeased.  COME ON! I had just come off of doing 60 down 46, and now this?

Anyway.

So Katie and I arrive at 'Mustang Country' and run through half the school until we find the team and actually get to warm up with everyone.  And then they start Congress crazy early, so Liz didn't get to attack Travis aka Pink Shirt. (Some hot junior from SHP, I think).  So we troop over to our room...and I totally beat Skillender out to PO.  (Well, we just agreed he'd do it next time.) So I did the morning session, and I ACTUALLY got a gavel.  I was so excited.  Sundeep made my day.  Anyway, I messed up a few times, but I covered for it well....I hope.

So then we get some crazy short lunch (ONLY 45 MINUTES!) because our chamber was huge- 23 voting members, and it got out of control.  We ran till 12 and had to be back by 12:45 so we could end at 3.  Liz POed the afternoon, and I made two speeches.  Oh man.  Be proud, Germaine.  SHP made yet another bill that demonstrated why they need to be able to spell BORDERS properly.  It's not boarders.  Ah well.  I authored ours and it was alright.

So we finally get out at like 3:15, so we missed all the other final rounds.  Liz, Katie, Zan and I all talked to Presner (Or Chaz, as he prefers to be called).  He's from SHP, and he totally saved my ass twice when I was POing.  Chaz is cool.  We played Egyptian Rat Screw, but then Liz and I had to leave cause she was driving me home and she had to go.

And then Katie calls me later and told me I got fourth, and Liz got fifth.  Originally I thought she said I got first and nearly hyperventilated.  But I got fourth.

Made the KatieKate's day.

So there ya go Germaine! Details!



AP Bio owns my soul.

Oh man, I'm back.  And before I dive right into my rant, Germaine, I need you to call me.  I deleted all my call logs by accident and I no longer have your cell, which makes me sad. -Tear- I could get it from Katie, but my call logs are not complete with my Germaine-y-kins' cell number, so if you get a chance, call me.

Okay.  And updates.  I can play soccer tomorrow, which has me so happy I can barely express it.  No, I can't express it.  I love the game, I love playing, and I finally can.  So happy.  And my dad came home from rehab where he went after he got out of the hospital, and it's really weird having him home, but he's been doing fine.  Aaannd...school's be alright so far, I'm upset cause I have only one class with JamieJame, but I have a few classes with Katie and Carleh and since we're still taking the same classes, we can still talk about them.  I'm pondering about switching over to physics from Constitution and American Legal Systems, but I'm not sure yet. I have my first AP Bio test tomorrow and two quizzes- lit and pre-cal.  Yeah, school's started again.

Still, this year hasn't exactly started out very well.  First I'm off my ankle for 6 weeks, destroying my half my season and my chances at varsity (well, starting off on varsity).  Then the next day my father goes into cardiac arrest, and everything changes.  The worst case predictions Jamie and I made came true, and it just seems like something's gotta give.  Of course there's good things, but with all these big bad things, I'm hoping for the really good thing that will make up for it.

And of course, the drama is starting already.  But the twist is, I simply don't care anymore.  I won't use names, because the girl I have issues with is, of course, a Mountie and basically all of you know her.  I'm not mad at her. I just don't want to be anywhere near her.  I'm so sick of all the harping on me, all the little digs, and all the nit-picking of my extensive faults.  I'm tired of the hypocrisy and the crazy insensitivity.  But you know, I could put up with all of that, I did.  But she wasn't there for me when I needed people, she who claims to be so close to me couldn't pick up a goddamn phone or IM me and ask 'Hey, how's your dad?  How are you?' 

No, not everyone inquired as to the health of my father and the mental health of my family and I, but if I brought it up they would ask.   They wouldn't feed me some line about praying for my family and then not say anything else about it.  Yes, I understand it's difficult to know what to say, because there is nothing to say.  But the way to show you care is not to not mention it.  This all showed me who my friends really were, and she just isn't one of them.

The sad thing is, I'm okay with that.  Our relationship was put under a lot of strain this year, by both of us, and I'm not going to say I'm not at fault.  I am, in part.  There were things I shouldn't have done or should have done.  But that doesn't vindicate her.  I'm sure she has lists of my myriad faults.  However, I just don't think it's worth it to put up with this from someone who's not there when I need it.

So now I'm just avoiding her, because I know this will come to a head, I know there will be a fight and it will be knock down, drag out, heavy and nasty.  But it will drag other people in, and I want to put that off as long as possible. I don't want them to have to deal with a fight, though I know it will happen, so I'll keep it at bay for now.

Yeah.  That's how it rolls.

Alright, I'm off, I'll stop bothering you all with the sordid details of my issues.

<3

After about 4 and a half months of having my permit, I broke the mold of my otherwise excellent driving and hit a fucking guardrail yesterday while trying to turn into the ICU parking lot.  It was not a fun experience.  Accidents have this weird way of completely screwing with your mind, even if the damage is minimal or it was just a mistake.

You see, you need to get a ticket at the parking lot, and being that I have short arms (cause I'm short...-tear-) I need to get the car really close to the machine.  So it was dark, and I was turning in, and I turned a little too hard.  With another car, I would have been fine.  But no, I was in my looong Volvo station wagon.  So the back door on my side had a rather unpleasant encounter with the guardrail.  Though, thinking back, why the fucking hell do they HAVE a guardrail there?  There's not one on the other side.  Damn assholes.  

But I was going maybe 5 miles an hour, so the door's a little scratched (but will probably come off in a car wash), and it's also dented in slightly, though you need to look at both doors to realize this.  There's this random strip of....something on my car, I guess it's plastic, and it serves no real purpose, but that needs to be reattached at the end to my car, but other than that, it's fine.

Still pisses me off though.

And I don't know what's happening with my father, I really don't.  Too many ups and downs for two weeks.  Soccer started yesterday.  Soz proclaimed himself the 'Uniform Nazi'.  And I swear to god, those were his exact words.  Teams get picked Sunday- maybe even Monday.

And that's all in the life of Katie.

My life is split into two complete opposites right now, and I don't hate it, but man is it surreal.  On one hand, I have my father- and anything involving him is instantly ten times more complicated.  Basically, he requires a quadruple bypass- I could go into the anatomy of it and why he really needs it, but it's unnecessary.  He needs it, he needs it now, and it could fix this problem.

However, because he's been in the hospital so long, he's actually gone crazy.  Since Wednesday night, he's had to be constantly sedated (completely or partially) and he's been in restraints.  He wants out, and we don't know if he'll let them do this surgery.  Actually, my mother thinks my father might want to just come home to die.  Which, needless to say, puts my whole family in a very uncomfortable position.  And I don't know what's right anymore, or what's for the best, I just don't know.  It all depends on what he says, and if they can declare him mentally incompatent, and what my mom decides...

So that's just a little stressful.  But then I have soccer starting tomorrow, and even though I can't play, I'm still excited.  I don't know if I'll make varsity or junior varsity...but we'll see.  As long as I can play, I'm happy.  I can go skating soon too...

But what makes me most happy are my friends.  Well, one friend in particular, my bestest friend in the whole world.  Somehow just talking to her makes everything seem okay, and I don't know how, but somehow she makes it sort of all better.  We always talk about how we're going to go to the same college, be room mates, work near each other, live next door to each other, be godparents to the others' kids...and I can't imagine that not working out. The thought of not being around her makes me feel like half of me is gone, and somehow just not the same at all. After all, she's my wonderwall.

I guess that's best friendship for you.  Whatever it is, it balances out the otherwise stressful existance I lead.  And right now...just being happy is enough. I <3 YOU ALL!

Last night, my father opened his eyes and woke up. He's already annoyed he can' move.

So I guess he'll be okay.

Okay, I think I'll make this relatively short, because I don't really know what to say but if I don't say it, no one will know because we're not in school.  If we were, everyone and her mother would have known about it.  But summer slows communication.

Yesterday my father was out bike riding and, as far as we know, stopped to fix a chain on his bike.  He then suffered a heart attack, the severity of which we still don't know.  As far as I know (the story gets a little shaky here) bystanders came to his aid and rescusitated him and called the paramedics.  Someone- the police, paramedics, or fire people- came and had to defib him.  So his heart stopped at least once and he stopped breathing as well.

They rushed him to Saint Barnabas, where he is now.  Supposedly his heart was shivering when they brought him in.  They stabilized him, and since yesterday evening he's been in the ICU there- well, technically the CCU (basically ICU for coronary patients) but we don't need to get that technical.  They gave him CAT scans to check for bleeding in his brain (a sign of a stroke), another to check his back, and a shitload of other tests, including EKGs and some enzymes test I haven't heard much about.  

From what I understand, the tests have confirmed there is damage to his heart, and the CAT scans have come back negative on the stroke.  My mother however mentioned they were worried about how long he had been without oxygen, but so far I haven't heard anything else about that.  I saw him in the ER and in the ICU last night, but he was heavily sedated.  He's intubated- has a tube down his throat to help him breath/breathing for him- he's attached to like 6 machines, has 2 IV lines, and a few other mismatched things.

But there were some positive signs today- he's moving, and supposedly he woke up, thought he didn't open his eyes.  We shall see, and I shall keep you guys updated.

Everyone's been really great, and my family is holding up okay.  Two of my uncles came down along with my grandma.  My mother keeps crying, but my brothers and I are still in shock. It's really surreal.

But I had my JamieJame over to keep my company last night, which I was beyond thankful for.  The ICU staff is really nice, and my coach happens to be a West Orange police officer so he's bringing my dad's bike and personal items here so we don't have to go back.  But those are just two examples of how awesome everyone is.

I'm going to go copy this into my xanga.  You can comment, call, email, whatever- or you don't have to. If you want to get in contact with me, you don't have to worry about it, but if you can't, not a big deal- I mean, it is pretty hectic around here, and I can't always talk long.

I love you all. ^^

Hola vosotros.  I'm at the JamieJame's house, and have been for like the past 30 hours.  Her family is having a party and one of her friends is here but is slightly anti-social or something, so I stole her computer and she's chilling in the basement with said friend.  Which really isn't a problem- what else is her friend supposed to do?  I've been here a while anyway.   

Last night I think I really realized how lucky I am.  I mean, everyone has shit in their lives, and I'm no exception.  My father's screwed up and obviously that's a lot of emotional stress. But I'm still so very lucky. (Jesus Christ this fucking keyboard hates me.  Musica.  Okay, I'm happy now).  I can't even put into words how thankful I am to have my JamieJame.  Obviously I'm beyond lucky to have the rest of my friends, but because I was with her, it was all the more poignant.  I couldn't ask for anything more in a friend, and I am one lucky bitch to have her.  I'm also extremely lucky to have all of my other friends too.  I don't know what I did to deserve them, but I thank my lucky stars every single day that I have them.  

Okay.  I needed a moment to reflect on what I have.  And I love it and I appreciate it.  I guess that's as good as it gets, right? Of courses.

I won't lie, there's still things I want. For instance...a guy.  Well, actually I think that's the only thing I really want that is even a possibility.  It does get pretty depressing being the only one of my group of friends who has yet to kiss a guy. For some reason, guys just don't seem to like me like that.  Or, when I finally find a guy who actually does feel an attraction for me, I simple can't reciprocate because I don't feel the same way about him.  And it really sucks sometimes, because then I feel bad- if I could like them, I would.  But love isn't some sort of switch you flip on and off.  I can't control who I fall for, and sadly I didn't fall for them. 

It's just the way it rolls sometimes, I guess.  One day I'll find the guy I want to be with, and he'll actually LIKE me.  Or maybe I've already found him and just don't know it yet.  Or maybe I'll meet him tomorrow. Or maybe.  Or maybe.  Sometimes all of these maybes piss me off- why can't I just love and be loved in return?  Is that such a difficult thing to find?  And then once I actually find a guy I like..what am I supposed to do?  I really only had one boyfriend I really cared for, and it wasn't exactly the experience to set anything else by.  Not that I don't love you Zak. But being your girlfriend did not teach me much about the way of guys.  

Doesn't help that I'm a friggin' coward either.  Oh well.  I will find a boyfriend this year- I will, I will, I will.  Maybe I've already found him.  We shall see.  Indeed we shall.

Alright, enough of my I WANT A GUY REALLY BADLY rant.  I think I shall go call my dear Jess when I get home and see when we shall go to Matt's house to swim again.  And I'm going to the doctor's on monday to hear the results of my MRI.  All shall be decided then FINALLY.  I'm so sick of waiting.

I love you all!

Oh man.  It's a record.  I haven't posted like this in my LJ in...forever.  My xanga's my journal.  But still.  I decided to be different today.

I spent a majority of yesterday complaining bitterly because my parents dragged my brothers and I up to Pennsylvania for no reason.  I love the house and I love being in the Poconos- but with a bad ankle, there's not much I can do.  My ankle is quite odd- sometimes I can walk on it with no pain, sometimes I have to do this weird limp/hobble, and other times I can't walk on it- hurts too much.

My MRI isn't until THURSDAY because of buerocratic nonsense.  Such a bitch.  I'm guessing since I can walk on it I didn't tear anything, but you never know.  I tried to jump on it yesterday.  Not fun. 

I keep going from 'I tore it, I tore something, I won't be able to play soccer, my season is over, I can't believe this, I'm going to go be depressed' and 'No, I can walk on it, it doesn't hurt, I'm fine, just a sprain, I'll tape it and brace it and DAMN RIGHT I AM PLAYING THIS YEAR'

But it still worries me.

My poor JamieJame needs to get her wisdom teeth removed on Wednesday.  I know I have them, but I don't know if I need to get them removed.  They still haven't come out of the gums, so I suppose I'm safe for now.  Plus, I only have two.  So that's good.

I can't believe it is the very last day of July.  Last year I couldn't WAIT for summer to end- everything I was looking forward to coincided with the beginning of school.  I wanted it over and done and gone.  Not this year.  I don't dread the coming of school- I'll get to see my friends, and it's not like I hate classes- but I rather like this relaxing thing I've heard so much about.  I should try it more often.

No, this summer seems perfect so far.  Not to fast, but not to slow.  The days just blend together.  I do enough things so not to be bored but not so many I'm stressing.  I'm already half way done with my AP Bio work and I've read the books for school- but I've done it in a very relaxed way.  Sort of.  For me.

And the way I see it, summer is half over.  We still have all of August- except we who play fall sports, but we still don't have to go to school.  And being the big, awesome juniors and seniors we are, we don't have to go to school until September 9th.  It's all good.

August shall be great.  Now if only I had the money to buy everyone presents who I need to buy presents for (or should have bought presents for)...wait, I babysit next week. Okay.  I'm good.

Thank god for two jobs

I've decided it is time to leave Peter behind.  I think we could have had something- but he's going to college in France, and he has a girlfriend.  It's impractical and silly to keep waiting for someone who might not even like me.  I'm the only one of my friends who hasn't had a boyfriend or even close this year.  Some of them are on their second or third.  So the KatieKate is moving on.

Speaking of such, there IS this hot guy from Seton Hall who's my friend Jessica's neighbor.  Kind of quiet, but I like him.  He interests me.  TO GERMAINE'S BROTHERS YEARBOOK!

Actually, Maxine, you know said hot guy from Seton Hall.  He works at the camp you work at.  I'll have to ask you about him.  

Not that I have a crush on him or anything- not yet- but he seems cool.  He's none to fond of Ryan Campi, so that's a good thing, I guess.  We shall see.  Germaine, don't worry, I've had weird dreams about Peter- really weird dreams.  And I won't lie, I probably do still like Peter a little.  But it's unrealistic.  

We will find FAR better guys, Germaine.  No worries.  None at all.  Guys who actually seem to get it, for instance.

Okay.  I need to go ice my ankle.  I rehurt it and haven't been able to walk on it- and after swimming today at Matt's (hot guy from SHP) pool, I could walk.  But now I can't.  Argh.

LOVE YOU ALL!

Germaine, I have bad news for you. I'm sorry. Katie: anyhow. before you leave for college, are you free anytime to hang out maybe? Peter: yeah, it think so Peter: we should set something up Peter: as for me, my girlfriend hates it when I am late, so I have to un Peter: run* Katie: okay Peter: I'll talk to you later Peter: be well Katie: sure, talk to you then Peter: goodnight Katie: you too Katie: 'night Peter: thanks Peter: night .... ARGH! Oh well. And...he's going to college...in FRANCE. It was doomed from the beginning. -Sigh- I just needed to tell you that Germaine. That's the end of that. I still want to hang out with him, but there's no way I can tell him now. Thank god he said that. Congress guys suck.

Oh man, I haven't updated in a while.  I like my xanga better.  It's the truth.  School's finally out and summer is here and jesus fucking christ wasn't it just September?  I can't believe it, I simply can't.  Germaine, I may be angsty (Well, if I'm happy, I generally don't post cause I don't need to) but YOU, my friend, are an online stalker! Angst and Stalker.  Bwahahah.

Oh, and every one loves the shirt.  Yeah.

So you all want to here about my life? Do ya? Do ya? Soccer is sorta boring but I'm so glad to be playing again, skating is a lot of work but we're moving forward, I <3 my friends, and somehow, even though school is over, I have an obnoxious amount of work to do.  DAMN YOU AP BIO! I'm also sinking into deep depression because I completely screwed up law of cosines on my algebra II final....no, wait, I'm not.

For the first time in a long while, I don't care.  I honestly don't.  It's no big deal I didn't get what I wanted on my algebra final. (Like my lowest test grade of the year....gods).  I don't want to think about chem, I don't even know where my AP Bio book is, lit and history are laughable and everything else I'm too relaxed to care about.

Or it's that I'm really tired.

ONE WEEK UNTIL LBI YEAH! I'm so happy to be going, it's going to be awesome fun.  Alright.  That's my life.  Perhaps I'll post again soon...

-<3333 KatieKate

These days are so beautiful they make me feel so lazy.  However, the goddamn orthapedic has basically sentanced me to house arrest.  Okay, so what if I was doing serious doubles on my sprained ankle?  I mean, if it's not going to get better, why can't I skate and enjoy myself?  I'm going to go friggin' nuts.  I can't skate for another two weeks.  Friggin'.  Nuts.

At least it's not soccer season.

I'm trying to do this Big Sister Little Sister Application but I fear I'm too lazy to actually do any real work on it.  I want everything to just magically transverse from my head to the paper, with no interim work by my fingers.  Is that really so much to ask?  Come on Ms. Burgess.  

You know what Germaine, I've never understood the obsession with tans either.  Do you know in India they do skin lightening treatments?  How weird is that?  Let me tell you, I'm pale, and I think I'd look weird any other way.  Cancer in a box is bad!  My dad had skin cancer, and I don't know what these guys are doing.  It's as bad as smoking.  Except smoking doesn't make you look good before you get cancer and die.

Anyway, I'm technically supposed to ask Peter today if he'll go to the mall with me so I can tell him I like him.  Nerve racking much?  I have so much to do though- tomorrow I'm babysitting and going to the mall, Saturday I have to ref (if Melanie ever calls me), go to the mall with him if he can go, go to Jess's party, and then sometime soon I need to do my chem lab, write my lit essay, and finish this application.

And maybe in between pick out my class ring and do something to ensure I do not get fat in 2 weeks from eating like I'm still actually doing exercise.  I hate not running around.  I know I'm not fat and not in any danger of it, but when I'm not doing something I feel so lethargic and lazy that it makes me feel bad about myself.  I need my goddamn endorphins from exercise!

But what can I do that doesn't involve my parents putting me under house arrest before I cause 'irreparable harm' to my ankle?

And yoga is out.

-Katie

Germaine told me to submit something to Golden Fleece.  So what do you guys think of this?

Scald away my imperfections
Burn them all to dust
Rip away my loyalties
Violate my trust
Beat my pride to the ground
Steal my confidence
Call it 'making me better'
Blame it on Providence
Tear away my worth
Drown my mind in tears
Kick around my beating heart
Misplace my dreams and fears
Humiliate my stubborn nature
Toss out my motivation
Make me the inhuman doll
When you blow away my determination
Twist me, turn me, wring me out
Forget happiness and sound
Annihilate the people I love
Allow my corruption to abound
Make me nothing, think you've won
Make a mockery of my sanity
Dig farther and farther till there's nothing left
Indulge and think you've beat me
But I'll come back, just you wait
Stronger than before you came
And I'll make you regret every word you said
I will not let you destroy me-I will not be ashamed

I dunno, most of the stuff I write is either too angsty, too many curses, or a tad too violent to submit.

But I promised Carleh anyway, so I might as well try to dig something up.  So there you are.

These ants (or this ant) keeps crawling on my leg and I keep freaking out.  I'm engrossed in looking at icons or talking to Zak and all of a sudden I get that creepy feeling and there's a big black ant on me.

I think I killed it though.

I've been really nostalgic lately.  Like, the Star Wars movie is coming out in less than a month- less than a month!  I can barely believe it.  I remember being in 7th grade and talking to Josh and Zak about it and wondering....wow....2005 is when the next movie comes out, what will I be like then?  EW I'LL BE OLD! 16! Or something like that, but whatever it was, it's creepy now.  

I miss it almost.  Almost.

Not that I don't love the Mount, but there was a comfort in Mt. Hebron too, and sometimes I miss it.  Anyway.

I think I have a plan to tell Peter that I like him.  I'm sick of this craziness- first I think the 'vibes', as Germaine put them, are there, then they're not, then maybe, then yes, then definitely not.  I might as well just ask him and get it over with.  Whats the worst thing that can happen?  He doesn't like me at all and I never have to see him again.

Germaine, just remind me about this so I don't chicken out.  

Okay, I need to go eat because I'm starved and I've been on the computer for like 2 hours. <3

I didn't get to finish my entry yesterday so I suppose I'll just continue it today. The funeral was so sad, everyone was crying- the row behind us was bawling the entire time. It wasn't as bad as it could have been though. I got weirdly disconnected, like I wasn't really there, like I really couldn't feel, which sort of scares me because I like being able to feel, and sometimes the numb is worse than the pain. But my father's been an absolute asshole, so maybe that's why I didn't feel anything. This morning he was driving recklessly and when I told him to stop doing that, he told me to get out of the car. This was after yelling at me because he said we wouldn't make it to the funeral in time, and I said we certainly would, and then he told me to stay out of it, because he was the driver. It's not even what he said, because I just tune it out. Or I was today, or trying. It's the fact he never, ever would have said that to me before. He'd only say that to my mom. With the funeral, I suppose I was concentrating on the things I've lost. And you know what, I don't care that it's not my family, as Katie said. She just doesn't understand- or she does, but she understands it how she sees it, and now how I feel it. It just doesn't matter. It doesn't matter when, or how, it matters that it will be, and sometime in the near future. It really frustrated me when she said that, like I should be grateful or something. You know what, maybe I should. But why am I supposed to be grateful that I still have a father who is abusive, dangerous, hurtful, and dying? Why should I be thankful that it isn't my father? It makes me sick, not relieved. Death just stole Chris's father from her, her father that was the same father from when she was 5, a father she loved and adored. And left me a father completely different, ravanged and almost hated as much as he is loved. Why didn't death take my father, not hers? Where is the justice? How come I'm supposed to feel better because death took the father that should have lived and is playing recklessly with the father who should have died? It's bullshit. It's all fucking bullshit. And I'm so fucking sick of dealing with it. And it's all so fucking unfair to boot.

I really don't want to go tomorrow, but I feel a twisted need to go, along with the fact it's the right thing to do.  Even though I don't really know Chris, I should still be there.  Plus, Jamie is close to her, and I can go for her too.  

The funeral is tomorrow for the father of a girl in my class, Chris.  It's particularly depressing for me, because it reminds me of everything I'm losing and everything I stand to lose, and even when we were in the chapel, my stomach was all twisted up and felt as if it were filled with ice cubes.  But strangely I feel depressed and anxious, but don't feel much at all.  For instance, when I heard about it from Mrs. T in the cafeteria, I left to go up to history, but it was sort of an automatic mode.

But why?  This doesn't happen often.  There's no reason for me to go on automatic without thinking something first.  Maybe it was an unconscious need to get out of there, to get away from it, maybe it was self-defense, I don't know.  I should be able to deal with this.  I will be able to deal with this.

Okay. Thanks. That helps my self esteem and confidence enormously. Makes me feel real great and completely ready to tell him I like him and have for quite a while now. Guys are so stupid.

I'm copying straight from my xanga, but I'm lazy and I've been lazy.  I'll do a new entry for livejournal soon, no worries people in LJ land.

I'm sick of always being the one to extend the hand, to make the call, to say hello, and so it's ending.  Not going to do it anymore.  I want it so badly it almost physically hurts and all I can think of is this but you don't seem to care.  And if you don't care, I can't keep hoping and hoping because it's breaking my heart and tearing me apart.

You mean more to me than my pride, my hope has beaten back my stubbornness.  But only for so long.  Why can't you see this?  Isn't it screamingly, blatantly obvious?  Please, stop playing with me like this.  Just let it start or let it end or let something happen, because this is driving me out of my mind.

It doesn't make sense, it must be something more if I still feel like this and still I don't move on.  But maybe I'm just an idiot.  Maybe I'm still grasping at strings when I should know better and just leave it be.  But what if it's not?  What if I regret it for forever?

But what if I regret this for forever?

Anyway.  Forensics yesterday was pretty tame.  I didn't write anything because I was a lazy ass and didn't feel like it.  I went just to be there with everyone, because for March I'll be at a skating competition instead so I'll be in a freezing cold rink, and all the seniors will be in Florida.  Germaine drove me- going 90 down 78.  That was fucking awesome.  Too bad we couldn't hit 100.

Anyway.  Congress itself was pretty boring, until they started talking about Iyer being a child molester, which was fucking hilarious.  I could not listen to anymore speeches about any of it anymore.  Still, I've spent my Saturdays in much more boring ways.  At least I was with my Mounties.  LAMBERT-COLE AND KATIE FOREVER!

After we were done, we went outside because I was antsy and I spent about 15 minutes throwing snowballs at Ridge.  I miss baseball so much.  Fuck softball, the goddamn ball is too big. It was a lot of fun, even though I kept breaking them or making them too heavy so that they hit the bench instead of the wall.

But I must say, I have not lost my skills.  I can still throw damn well.  Maybe a little high, but I'm not used to throwing short distances without someone there with a goddamn mitt.  I wish I could play again, but there's no way I'm dealing with those Nazi's, and being able to throw isn't enough. 

What else happened.....oh yes.  Spitzer needs to learn how to tuck his shirt into his PANTS.  Not his BOXERS.

Alrighty, it's dinner time.  Have fun everyone, I <3 you all.

I'm in a depresseded, morbid about the future, pessimistic mood.  And I rather liked how it came out on my xanga, so I decided to copy and paste- yes, the horror of my cheating ways- and put it here too. Cause I've been lazy lately.

It's really scary, you know.  It's horrifying to look at these things and read these listings and check every single one in your mind.  I don't know how to deal with myself, I feel so bad asking other people to deal with me.  How can I expect something of someone else when I can't expect it of myself?  It seems sorta screwed up,definatly hypocritical, but I can't let go of human contact entirely.

2 more years, one more month, and 18 more days. 

I just hope this doesn't make me bitter or cynical.  I think it has already.  It's changed me already, it's altered the way I see things, it's messed with how I deal with things.  I see people freaking out about such little things, such crazy shit, and I need to restrain myself from yelling at them.  They seem so shallow to me, so dependent, so set up for the fall, and then I feel worse because who am I to judge them?

Does my suffering allow me to pass judgements on another? Does my twisted existence push me above another and give me the right to tell them that they need to chill out and take a few steps back? Does the hell that is my life somehow vindicate me from hypocrisy?

This is why sometimes I think it's better guys don't seem to be attracted to me.  I don't have time for them.  If I wrap myself up in intricacies, if I surround myself with the abstract, if I throw myself into the only thing I feel is worth doing, then the emotions and insanity of everyday life seem to fade away.  If no one loves me, I don't have to worry about getting hurt.  If no one wants to be with me, I don't have to concerned with being sidetracked.

I can just lose myself in my work, lose myself to the world, because my days are numbered, I can feel it in my bones.  I pray every night that it is not my brothers, but me with it, that somehow by some miracle that if any of us had to inheirited the curse that it is me not them.  Better yet that none of us have it, but that is foolish to even hope that, it is lunacy to even wish that.

Because I can handle it and they can't.  Because better that I take it, better that I suffer then them. Better that I become him, better that I do what he should have, then my brothers being forced along that path. Better that I accomplish what I came here to do and leave the world a better place with no husband sobbing and no children wailing while they scatter what was once me along the waves.  

It is better.

Isn't it?

Sunday, October 24, 2004

 October 24, 2004



Alrighty, I have a lot to write, I've had a busy weekend and I'm still wired on three and a half hours of sleep so I have the energy to write.  Yeah.  Be afraid.

SO.

On Friday was JamieJame's party, which was awesome.  I needed that party, I felt so wired and happy, even though I felt a little quesy. Come to think of it, I've been off and on sick.  Really annoying.  Anyway, I had a ball dancing with my Mounties- except Jamie, who kept ditching me for other people.  I was so not appreciated.

Then she did the candle lighting, and it was so sweet! I shared and candle with like 6 other people- it was the Mount candle, for all the people Jamie couldn't fit on the other candles, but I did get my own little speech.  She COMPLETELY outed me about cheating on her with Mrs. Marin. I TOLD YOU ALREADY! IT WAS A MISUNDERSTANDING! (I cheated on her with Congress guy.  Come on)

It was just hilarious, I nearly fell out of my chair laughing.  And I had a very interesting conversation with Luis and him making some shit up about me and Napalm- which actually intrigued me.  Explosions always make me feel happy and not sappy.

I had like 4 strawberry 'frozen drinks' which were really virgin daquerri's, however you spell it, and I don't think they agreed with me. 

Oh, did I mention how awesome everyone else looked? My make up decided to hate me, but Jamie looked...un Jamie like.  I loved her hair and her dress.  Seriously.  Really intricate hairstyles amuse me, and I'm very glad she's my size as well, so I can steal her dress. Bwahaha.

Anyway. All good things must end, and my father got me at 11 and I went home and drifted off, blissfully unaware of how badly I would screw up the next day at forensics.

It started off pretty normal.  No breakfast, just got dressed and ready, got my thing of tea, and off we go.  We got Katie and went to Montville- actually, a really, really pretty place.  Right next to mountains, and sort of rural- I loved it. At first.

Then I started feeling sick.  Not uncommon.  I attribute it to the tea.  It makes my stomach queasy.  And then low and behold, my day picks up.

HE CAME.

Yeah.  They sent in their bill like 3 different ways, but it never got to us, so Congress guy had to compete in Varsity Extempt, which I am so jealous of, because he just seems to be able to switch from event and event and do well EVERYWHERE.

Argh.

So I talked to him for a little and it made me feel better.  We were talking about placings and that sort of thing and how there weren't that many good people in the chamber and I would place. Famous last words, man.

And off he goes and I met the new Congress girl from Vernon.  I like her.  I talked too much, but I think it's awesome we have new people.  Come to think of it, I acted obnoxious at forensics, but I don't know why.  I didn't always....I was just too....I don't know.

I can't talk to anyone. It wasn't my mother who died, but for some reason, these thoughts won't leave me alone.  My mind is a whirl but I can't do anything about it.  The deaths seem to be adding on, growing ever closer, in time, in relationship to me.  I may just be paranoid, but it makes sense in my head, and right now that's all I care about.

What's scary is for a moment I was jealous of Lindsay's mother, who died.  That shocked me to the core and now I don't even trust myself. 

As people go, the first person I knew who died was my Pop-pop.  I was 9.  I never really knew hi-- I just realized this is just like Lovely Bones.  Anyway.  I never knew him.  I was frightened of him.  I'd hear stories about him, every once in a while.  My mother is a storyteller, but for some reason she doesn't talk about him much.  Next was my Aunt Mill, who knew only that I was Joe's oldest.  I hear lot's of stories about her, though.  I was...what...11? Maybe 12.  

Neither of these affected me much.  

Then my Uncle John, who's actually my great uncle, got hit by a car.  They couldn't even get his name right in the paper, isn't that sad? I don't think it's ever sunk in he's dead, we haven't been back since.  Added to that, the time before that, I remember him yelling at me or something, so my conscious realizes it, but I don't.

That didn't make sense.  Whatever. I was 13. 13? Yes. 13. Had to be.

Then my grandfather died.  This happened this past December.  He's been dead to me for so long, though.  He was an abusive alchoholic, and I haven't seen him alive since I was 9.  I was 14.  Everyone was upset- or most were- but of course, how are me and my brothers to get upset if we never knew him?

Now the relevence of that.

Looking up, not one of those has affected me very much.  Death has not touched me.  It lurks, everpresent above my father, the lack of it causing pain and then causing even more when I realize what that means.  But other then that, I have been strangely spared, and instead of feeling lucky, I feel like I've cheated Death.  

I'm so afraid, so very afraid that once Death does reach into my life that it will be taking away someone close to me, someone I rely on.  That I will suffer for the years I did not.  And little by little, they do.

My pop-pop and aunt were pretty close in actual affect on me; my parents were upset, but today I feel nothing saying that they're dead.  My uncle inched a little closer, because it hasn't sunk in, and I can still see him smiling and playing cards with us.  My grandfather, I never knew in person, but of my grandparents, he's undoubtably had the greatest, and will have the greatest affect on my life, though it's negative in it's entirety.

Abusive behavior transcends generations and haunts more then just the direct children.  I remember, be it true or false, my father throwing my brother against the first landing of the stairs.  I do remember the violent fights.  That is my grandfather's fault.

And even more then that, it is his cursed genes my father has, that maybe I have, that I'm so sure I do have, that are ripping my family apart, seam by seam, faster then my mother can sew it.  Because of that shadow, I cannot have children, not until I know.  Never until I know.

And now Lindsay's mother, which frightens me for Lindsay and because Lindsay does call me mom sometimes, so I feel a distant kinship with her.

Oh, this is such nonsense. Why do you care, dear reader? Why do you want to see into the mind of one who is over exaggerating her scars, one who lies, one who pretends never to cry, one who forgot her past and now is doomed to forever wonder if for that long she has been lying to herself.

Why?
